msgid ""
"By default &kmail; will show &HTML; messages in plain text. If you prefer to "
"view messages with &HTML; formatting and layout automatically, select this "
"option. However, we recommend leaving this option off, as security problems "
"with &HTML; might show up."
msgstr ""
"Vaikimisi näitab &kmail; &html;-kirju lihttekstina. Kui eelistad näha kirju "
"automaatselt algupärases &html;-vormingus ja -esituses, märgi see valik. "
"Siiski soovitame tungivalt jätta selle sisse lülitamata, sest see võib kaasa "
"tuua tõsiseid &html;-iga seotud turvaprobleeme."

#. Tag: para
#: configure.docbook:2076
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "You can still easily view messages in &html; format per email by clicking "
#| "the plain message/html message toggle bar on the left hand side of the "
#| "message window. Please see <link linkend=\"configure-appearance-message-"
#| "window\">Message Window</link> to enable this feature."
msgid ""
"You can still easily view messages in &HTML; format by clicking the plain "
"message/HTML message toggle bar on the left hand side of the preview pane."
msgstr ""
"Siiski saab konkreetset kirja hõlpsasti näha &html;-vormingus, kui klõpsata "
"lugemisakna vasakus servas lihttekstis ja HTML-kirja lülitamise ribale. "
"Täpsemalt kõneleb sellest osa <link linkend=\"configure-appearance-message-"
"window\">Lugemispaneel</link>."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: configure.docbook:2084
#, no-c-format
msgid "Allow messages to load external references from the Internet"
msgstr "Võrgust väliste viidete laadimine"

#. Tag: para
#: configure.docbook:2086
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If checked, &kmail; can load external images, stylesheets &etc; from the "
#| "Internet when you look at an &html; message. We strongly recommend to "
#| "leave this option off (although it has no effect if you only view plain "
#| "text messages)."
msgid ""
"If checked, &kmail; can load external images, style sheets, &etc; from the "
"Internet when you view an &HTML; message. We strongly recommend that you "
"leave this option off (although it has no effect until you enable &HTML;)."
msgstr ""
"Sisselülitamisel võib &kmail; laadida internetist pilte, laaditabeleid "
"&etc;, kui vaatad &html;-kirja. Me soovitame tungivalt selle võimaluse "
"keelata (kuigi see ei toimi niikuinii, kui vaatad ainult puhta tekstiga "
"kirju)."

#. Tag: para
#: configure.docbook:2091
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "By adding external references to their messages, people sending spam can "
#| "detect when you have looked at their message, your location, and alot of "
#| "other information that gets logged on web servers. Note that this option "
#| "has no effect on &Java;, JavaScript and Plugins as these are not "
#| "supported in &kmail; at all, which is a good thing, as most viruses "
#| "propagate through these."
msgid ""
"By adding external references to their messages, people sending spam can "
"detect when you have looked at their message, your location, and a lot of "
"other information that may get logged on web servers. Note that this option "
"has no effect on &Java; or JavaScript, as these are not supported in &kmail; "
"at all."
msgstr ""
"Väliste viidete lisamisega kirjadele saavad rämpsposti saatjad tuvastada, et "
"sa oled nende kirja vaadanud, samuti seda, millal sa seda tegid, sinu "
"asukohta ja veel paljut muudki. Arvesta, et see võimalus ei ole seotud "
"&Java;, JavaScripti ja pluginatega - need on nagunii keelatud ega kuulu "
"mingil juhul rakendamisele, mis on hea, sest enamik viirusi just nii levibki."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: configure.docbook:2102
#, no-c-format
msgid "Informs if message reading is a suspected email scam"
msgstr "Teavitamine, kas loetav kiri võib olla petukiri"

#. Tag: para
#: configure.docbook:2104
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "With the popularity of email, unfortunately comes the popularity of email "
#| "scams. Email scams can include emails made to appear as though they come "
#| "from legitimate companies, but they really link to malicious web sites "
#| "requesting your personal information. This can lead to identity theft and "
#| "worse. By default &kmail; analyzes messages for common scams, and will "
#| "inform you if the email is a suspected scam. It is highly advised to keep "
#| "this feature enabled. If you wish to disable this great feature, uncheck "
#| "<guilabel>Informs if message reading is a suspected email scam</guilabel>."
msgid ""
"As email has become more popular, email scams have proliferated. Email scams "
"may include emails made to appear as if they come from legitimate companies, "
"even though they really link to malicious web sites requesting your personal "
"information. This may lead to identity theft, and worse. By default &kmail; "
"analyzes messages for common scams, and will inform you if a message is a "
"suspected scam. We recommend that you keep this feature enabled. If you wish "
"to disable these warnings, uncheck <guilabel>Informs if message reading is a "
"suspected email scam</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"E-kirjade menu levimisega on paraku käsikäes käinud rämpsposti ja "
"petukirjade levik. Nende hulka kuulub selliseid kirju, mis esmapilgul "
"paistavad täiesti ehtsana, aga sisaldavad siiski linke pahatahtlikele "
"veebilehekülgedele, mis nõuavad sinu isiklikke andmeid. Sellega võib "
"kaasneda identiteedivargus või midagi hullematki. Vaikimisi analüüsib "
"&kmail; kirju, et tuvastada levinumad rämpsposti liigid, ning annab teada, "
"kas kiri võib olla petukiri. Äärmiselt soovitatav on see jätta see valik "
"märgituks. Kui sa aga mingil põhjusel siiski seda ei soovi, eemalda märge "
"valiku <guilabel>Teavitamine, kas loetav kiri võib olla petukiri</guilabel> "
"eest."

#. Tag: para
#: configure.docbook:2113
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If you have legitimate emails being flagged, &eg; from trusted friends, "
#| "you can add their email to the <guilabel>Whitelist:</guilabel> by "
#| "clicking the <guibutton>Add...</guibutton> and enter the email into the "
#| "dialog that pops up. Please note that at this time, only individual "
#| "emails are supported."
msgid ""
"If legitimate emails are being flagged, (&eg;, from trusted friends), you "
"can add their email addresses to the <guilabel>Whitelist:</guilabel> by "
"clicking the <guibutton>Add...</guibutton> button and entering an address "
"into the dialog that pops up. Please note that at this time, only complete "
"email addresses can be whitelisted."
msgstr ""
"Kui sellist kahtlust avaldatakse mõne kirja suhtes, mis on igati puhas, &eg; "
"mõnelt usaldusväärselt sõbralt, võid lisada nende kirjad <guilabel>valgesse "
"nimekirja</guilabel>, klõpsates nupule <guibutton>Lisa...</guibutton> ja "
"kirjutades e-posti aadressi ilmuvasse dialoog. Palun arvesta, et praegu on "
"toetatud ainult lisamine ühe aadressi kaupa."

#. Tag: guilabel
